"Implement the following plan:\n\n# Plan: Fix prompt.txt missing in mid-turn commit checkpoints\n\n## Context\n\nMid-turn commits (agent commits while still working) produce checkpoints without `prompt.txt` after the first one. All checkpoints in a turn share the same user prompt and should all have it.\n\nRoot cause: `extractCheckpointPrompts()` scopes the transcript past where the prompt lives after the first condensation advances `CheckpointTranscriptStart`.\n\n## Approach\n\nRepurpose `FirstPrompt` on session state to track the **last prompt** instead. Update it on every `InitializeSession` call (each `UserPromptSubmit`). Use it in condensation instead of re-parsing the transcript.\n\nAll consumers of `prompt.txt` already truncate (`ExtractFirstPrompt` → 60 chars), and `FirstPrompt` stores 100 runes, so the truncation is fine.\n\n## Changes\n\n### 1. Rename `FirstPrompt` → `LastPrompt` in session state\n\n**`cmd/entire/cli/session/state.go`** (line 142-143):\n- Rename field from `FirstPrompt` to `LastPrompt`\n- Keep JSON tag as `\"first_prompt\"` for backward compat with existing state files\n- Update comment\n\n### 2. Update `LastPrompt` on every turn, not just the first\n\n**`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go`** — `InitializeSession()` (line ~1681-1684):\n\nChange from only-backfill-if-empty:\n```go\nif state.FirstPrompt == \"\" && userPrompt != \"\" {\n    state.FirstPrompt = truncatePromptForStorage(userPrompt)\n}\n```\nTo always-update:\n```go\nif userPrompt != \"\" {\n    state.LastPrompt = truncatePromptForStorage(userPrompt)\n}\n```\n\n**`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_session.go`** — `initializeSession()` (line ~241):\n- Rename `FirstPrompt:` → `LastPrompt:` in the initial state struct\n\n### 3. Use `LastPrompt` in condensation\n\n**`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go`**:\n\n`extractSessionData()` (line ~465) and `extractSessionDataFromLiveTranscript()` (line ~504):\n\n```go\nif state.LastPrompt != \"\" {\n    data.Prompts = []string{state.LastPrompt}\n} else {\n    data.Prompts = extractCheckpointPrompts(...)\n}\n```\n\n`extractSessionData` doesn't receive state directly — it receives individual fields. Add `turnPrompt string` parameter, pass `state.LastPrompt` from the caller (`CondenseSession` at line 129).\n\n`extractSessionDataFromLiveTranscript` already receives `state *SessionState`, so just use `state.LastPrompt`.\n\n### 4. Use `LastPrompt` in `finalizeAllTurnCheckpoints`\n\n**`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go`** (line ~2017):\n\n```go\nvar prompts []string\nif state.LastPrompt != \"\" {\n    prompts = []string{state.LastPrompt}\n} else {\n    prompts = extractUserPrompts(state.AgentType, string(fullTranscript))\n}\n```\n\n### 5. Update references\n\nRename `FirstPrompt` → `LastPrompt` in:\n- `cmd/entire/cli/status.go` (line 311) — display\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_types.go` (line 17-24) — constant and helper comment\n- `cmd/entire/cli/status_test.go` — test fixtures\n\n### 6. Fix reverted integration test\n\n`cmd/entire/cli/integration_test/manual_commit_workflow_test.go` was reverted and still references `context.md`. Update:\n- `TestShadow_FullTranscriptContext`: Remove context.md assertions\n- `TestShadow_RewindAndCondensation`: Remove context.md assertions\n- `TestShadow_FullTranscriptCondensationWithIntermediateCommits`: Update to expect all prompts present (since LastPrompt provides them)\n\n### 7. Update/add tests\n\n- Verify mid-turn checkpoints have prompt.txt\n- Verify `LastPrompt` is updated on each turn\n\n## Verification\n\n1. `mise run fmt && mise run test:ci`\n2. Manual: mid-turn commit scenario → all checkpoints get prompt.txt\n\n\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/gtrrz-victor/.claude/projects/-Users-gtrrz-victor-wks-cli-cli/fed731da-f6c2-4597-8913-6f415974c950.jsonl"